    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Interview Question Generator\\n\",\"**NLP Project 60 of 100** — Generate role-specific interview questions from job descriptions.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import re, requests, numpy as np\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nrng = np.random.default_rng(42)\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"QUESTION_BANK = {\\n    'Python': ['Explain the difference between lists and tuples.','What are decorators?','How does garbage collection work?'],\\n    'SQL': ['What is the difference between INNER and LEFT JOIN?','Explain indexing strategies.','How do you optimize slow queries?'],\\n    'Machine Learning': ['Explain bias-variance tradeoff.','What is cross-validation?','How do you handle imbalanced classes?'],\\n    'System Design': ['Design a URL shortener.','How would you scale a real-time chat system?','Design a recommendation engine.'],\\n    'Behavioral': ['Tell me about a time you handled a difficult project.','How do you prioritize tasks?','Describe a technical disagreement.'],\\n}\\n\\ndef generate_questions(jd_text, n=5):\\n    skills = []\\n    for skill in QUESTION_BANK:\\n        if skill.lower() in jd_text.lower():\\n            skills.append(skill)\\n    if not skills: skills = ['Behavioral']\\n    \\n    questions = []\\n    for _ in range(n):\\n        skill = rng.choice(skills)\\n        q = rng.choice(QUESTION_BANK[skill])\\n        questions.append(f'[{skill}] {q}')\\n    return questions\\n\\njd = 'We need a Machine Learning Engineer with strong Python and SQL skills. Experience with system design preferred.'\\nprint(f'JD: {jd}\\\\n')\\nfor q in generate_questions(jd, 6):\\n    print(f'  • {q}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# LLM-based generation\\ndef llm_questions(jd, model='qwen3:1.7b'):\\n    prompt = f'Generate 5 interview questions for this role. Mix technical and behavioral. Output numbered list only.\\\\n\\\\nJob: {jd} /no_think'\\n    try:\\n        r = requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/generate',json={'model':model,'prompt':prompt,'stream':False},timeout=60)\\n        return r.json().get('response','')\\n    except: return 'Ollama unavailable.'\\n\\nprint('\\\\nLLM-generated questions:')\\nprint(llm_questions(jd))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Skill extraction from JDs drives relevant question selection.**\\n\",\"- **Question banks ensure consistent, vetted content.**\\n\",\"- **LLMs generate tailored questions** for unusual roles.\\n\",\"- **For production, categorize questions** by difficulty and competency.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
